<DOC><DOCNO> AP881124-0046 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-24-88 0718EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     11-24 0376</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0387</SECOND><HEAD>Snow Advisories Issued For Several Western, Midwestern States</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Snow advisories were posted this morning for the mountains ofeastern Oregon and California, and parts of Idaho, Utah, Montana,Wyoming and North Dakota.   For the mountains of Southern California and for northernArizona, advisories also were issued for gusty winds.   Snow extended from south-central Montana across northern andwestern Wyoming, eastern Idaho, northern Utah and northern Nevada.The biggest reported snowfall for the six hours ended 1 a.m. EST was4 inches at Reno, Nev.   Rain lingered this morning along the northern and central PacificCoast, from eastern Montana into western North Dakota, as well aseastern Florida, Georgia, and along the central Atlantic Coast.   Today's weather forecast called for rain along the northern halfof the Pacific Coast and across the central part of the Dakotas;snow from the western part of the Dakotas across the upper MissouriValley and the Rockies.   Predicted highs: 20s and 30s in New England, northern Minnesota,North Dakota and the Rockies; 40s and 50s from New York state acrossVirginia, the Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, the upper MississippiValley, South Dakota, Nebraska, and the northern two-thirds of thePacific Coast; 80s in southern Florida and southern Texas.   The rest of the nation should generally be in the 60s and 70s.   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 15 degrees atHoulton, Maine, to 75 at Key West, Fla.   Other reports:   _East: Atlanta 45 fair; Boston 30 cloudy; Buffalo 26 partlycloudy; Charleston, S.C. 50 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 29 fair;Cleveland 27 fair; Detroit 27 foggy; Miami 70 foggy; New York 35fair; Philadelphia 34 fair; Pittsburgh 27 fair; Portland, Maine 25fair; Washington 36 fair.   _Central: Bismarck 23 cloudy; Chicago 37 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth45 fair; Denver 58 windy; Des Moines 41 fair; Indianapolis 35 fair;Kansas City 46 windy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 38 partly cloudy;Nashville 32 fair; New Orleans 44 foggy; St. Louis 41 fair.   _West: Albuquerque 36 fair; Anchorage 15 cloudy; Las Vegas 55windy; Los Angeles 53 partly cloudy; Phoenix 55 fair; Salt Lake City33 snow; San Diego 58 drizzle; San Francisco 48 cloudy; Seattle 38windy.   _Canada: Montreal 23 cloudy; Toronto 30 partly cloudy.</TEXT></DOC>